The Lagos State chapter of the All Progressives Congress has inaugurated the screening and screening appeal committees. The party said the move was in preparation for the upcoming local government election scheduled for July. The state chairman, Tunde Balogun, said this on Tuesday during the event at the Lagos State APC secretariat, Ikeja. Balogun said, “I charge the two committee members to deliver their assignments with integrity and diligence to aid the emergence of credible flag-bearers for the party in the forthcoming election.” The chairman of the screening committee, Prof. Abayomi Etti, expressed his appreciation for the opportunity to serve and contribute his quota to the development of democracy. He also assured party members of the committee’s readiness to deliver on its assignment. The chairman of the screening appeal committee, Otunba Femi Pedro, thanked the members for the opportunity to demonstrate his experience and guarantee the execution of the committee duties. Members of the screening committee are Mr Babatunde Ogala (Vice Chairman), Adetoun Adediran (secretary), Prof. Adeniyi Harrison and Oyinlomo Danmole. Those of the screening appeal committee are Folasade Bakare (secretary), Sejoro James, Rasaq Balogun and Dele Oloke. Copyright PUNCH. All rights reserved. This material, and other digital content on this website, may not be reproduced, published, broadcast, rewritten or redistributed in whole or in part without prior express written permission from PUNCH. Contact: theeditor@punchng.com